        <body>
            <div type="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa"><!-- no file from ms; this text from printed copy; compare carefully against ms -->
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>It was an eve of summer, mild<add rend="line_number-JR">890</add></l>
                    <l>As ever looked the pale moon through</l>
                    <l>That the deep waters were beguiled</l>
                    <l>Into such rest, that as the blue,</l>
                    <l>The moveless blue of the high heaven</l>
                    <l>Such sleep was to the <subst><add place="above">low lake</add><del rend="strikethrough">waters</del></subst> given<add rend="line_number-JR">895</add></l>
                    <l>That as in lethargy it lay</l>
                    <l>Waveless and tideless, soft and grey</l>
                    <l>As chasmless glacier, Voicelessly</l>
                    <l>The little barks came gliding by</l>
                    <l>Apparently without a wind<add rend="line_number-JR">900</add></l>
                    <l>Leaving long ripply wakes behind,</l>
                    <pb facs="MSVIII65r"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top-right"><handShift new="#HANDWGC" medium="pencil"/>65</fw>
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>It would have seemed a lifeless sea</l>
                    <l>But there arose colossally</l>
                    <l>Beyond the mist horizon, where,</l>
                    <l>The waters mingled with the air<add rend="line_number-JR">905</add></l>
                    <l>The spirits of gigantic things,&#x2014;</l>          
                    <l>Lords of the earth and air and sky.</l>
                    <l>Where <del rend="strikethrough">the</del> white heaven&#x02BC;s cloud in his gathering <add place="above">around them</add> flings</l><!--this addition is peculiar, please check-->
                    <l>Concealment everlastingly</l>
                    <l>The mountain snow, like scattered flocks<add rend="line_number-JR">910</add></l> 
                    <l>Speckled on high the red ribbed rocks,</l> 
                    <l>Or down the ravines rolling blue</l> 
                    <l>Its crisped surge oer the green fields threw</l> 
                    <l>Flinging the icewaves far and wide</l> 
                    <l>Like the tortured spray of the ocean tide<add rend="line_number-JR">915</add></l> 
                    <l><subst><add>Breaking broad on the mountain side.</add><del rend="strikethrough">On the <!--???--> green of the <!--???--> and mountain side</del></subst></l> 
                    <l>Yet was there such a softness shed</l> 
                    <l>Upon the rude <geogName corresp="#ALPS">alps</geogName>&#x02BC; stormy head</l> 
                    <l>On massive wood and <subst><add>russet</add><del rend="strikethrough">stormy</del></subst> brake</l> 
                    <l>Flashing river and polished <del>g</del> lake<add rend="line_number-JR">920</add></l> 
                    <!--<l>So broadly stretched in sapphire sheet,&#x2014;</l> 
                    <l>Another heaven beneath our feet</l> 
                    <l>Of deeper, darker, lovelier blue,&#x2014;</l> 
                    <l>It seemed that we were looking through</l> 
                    <l>Those aether fields, so pure, so high,<add rend="line_number-JR">925</add></l> 
                    <l>Above the concave of the sky,</l> 
                    <l>Where nor storm nor tempest cometh nigh,</l> 
                    <l>And the moon she sits in her majesty.</l> 
                    
                    the above lines are missing from MS VIII or are, at least, not following on the same page-->
                    
                </lg>
